sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
A Job is a runnable task that is controlled/monitored by Jenkins. This action creates a new job from a configuration XML on the Jenkins Server.

Inputs:

  • Job Name - Name of the Job to be created.
  • XML Job Definition - Provide job configuration in XML format. E.g. ... .
  • Parent Folder Path - Path of your parent folder under which you want to create your new job. E.g. UAT-jobs/web-apps.

Outputs:

  • Status - Will be set to “Success" if the request succeeds or “Error" if a failure occurs.
  • Error Message - Will be populated when the status is "Error".

Error Messages:

  • You do not have enough permissions to perform this action in Jenkins server.
  • The request could not be fulfilled due to invalid characters in job name.
  • The Jenkins server is being restarted.
  • Invalid username or password/token.
  • A job name already exists with the given name.
  • Job Name does not match the job name convention pattern.
  • The request could not be fulfilled due to bad XML syntax.
  • Parent folder path doesn't exists or not accessible.

Additional Notes:

  • Provide encoded 'XML Job Definition' in case of special characters in it.
  • If the 'XML Job Definition' has any particular plugin steps, make sure you have installed that plugin in your Jenkins Server otherwise, the job will be created successfully without plugin steps in its configuration.
  • If Parent Folder is not specified then the new job will be created on the top level of Jenkins.

To use this action, the corresponding Jenkins connection and credential must be created and associated with the Jenkins Connection & Credential alias.

Disclaimer:Jenkins and Jenkins logo are a registered trademark of Jenkins.

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
sys_hub_action_type_definition.name: Create Job
